    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1371_journal_pcbi_1011912__task_005/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card frames a validation study ('Extend PCPFM batch correction step to validate pycombat output...') that goes beyond the paper's scope. The paper demonstrates batch correction as part of the pcpfm pipeline workflow but does not present it as a standalone validation study with explicit preservation-of-integrity and variance-reduction metrics.",
        "The card's research question implies a hypothesis-testing study design ('Does batch correction preserve...'), whereas the paper presents batch correction as an implemented feature with qualitative demonstration of effectiveness on one dataset (HZV029 Plasma RP-).",
        "The expected outputs specify a structured quantitative validation report with specific metrics (sample count, feature count, pre/post variance estimates for \u22655 features), which is not described in the paper. The paper shows visual QC outputs (PCA, TICs, clustermaps) but not the tabular validation report format implied by the card."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_005",
