      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Empirical compounds are constructed from a feature table using Khipu [44] and most methods for empirical compounds concern annotation... MS1-based annotations are generated using our JSON metabolite services library and appropriately formatted inputs or m/z and retention time similarity to authentic standards.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms khipu uses adduct definitions and annotation rules, but does not explicitly state that ionization mode is inferred from metadata to select these definitions. The paper does not document ionization polarity as a configurable input to khipu.",
